description: Start in a plank position, lower your body until your chest nearly touches the floor, then push back up.
Stand with feet shoulder-width apart, lower your hips down and back as if sitting on a chair, then stand back up.
Hold a push-up position with your weight on your forearms, elbows, and toes.
Step forward with one leg and lower your hips until both knees are bent at about a 90-degree angle.
From a standing position, drop into a squat, kick your feet back into a plank, return to squat, and jump up.
Start in a plank position, bring one knee towards your chest, then switch legs in a running motion.
Lie on your back, pedal your legs in the air while reaching your opposite elbow towards each knee.
Sit on the edge of a chair, lower your body by bending your elbows, then push back up.
Jump with your legs spread and arms reaching overhead, then return to a standing position.
Run in place, bringing your knees up to hip level with each step.
